<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Shrew1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Shrew,</orth> subst. (often spelt <emph>shrow</emph> in O. Edd. and always pronounced so; cf. the rhymes in <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.46" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.213" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 213</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 5.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 28</bibl>. 188) a vixen, a scold: <bibl n="shak. err 4.1.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 1, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.46" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 5.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.315" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 315</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 22</bibl>. 87 <cit><quote>(he is more s. than she).</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 22</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 5.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 5.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 28</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 5.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 28</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.3.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 3, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.3.36" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 3, 36</bibl>.
